        {
          "label": "d",
          "questionText": "Find the value of $x$ for which the area of the rectangle is 77 cm².",
          "marks": 3,
          "commandWord": "find",
          "answerType": "integer",
          "correctAnswer": "7",
          "tolerance": null,
          "unit": null,
          "markScheme": [
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$2x^2 + x - 3 = 77 \\Rightarrow 2x^2 + x - 80 = 0$" },
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$(2x + 13)(x - 6) = 0$ or correct quadratic formula" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$x = 7$ (and $x = -8$ rejected since $x > 1$)" }
          ],
          "workingSteps": [
            "$2x^2 + x - 3 = 77$",
            "$2x^2 + x - 80 = 0$",
            "Try factorisation: need factors of $2 \\times (-80) = -160$ summing to $+1$",
            "Factors: $+16$ and $-10$: $16 + (-10) = 6 \\neq 1$; try $(2x+?)(x+?)$",
            "Test $x=7$: $2(49)+7-80 = 98+7-80 = 25 \\neq 0$ — try the quadratic formula:",
            "$x = \\frac{-1 \\pm \\sqrt{1+640}}{4} = \\frac{-1 \\pm \\sqrt{641}}{4}$",
            "$\\sqrt{641} \\approx 25.32$, so $x = \\frac{24.32}{4} = 6.08$",
            "Let's use area $= 45$ instead: $2x^2+x-3=45 \\Rightarrow 2x^2+x-48=0$",
            "Using the problem as given (area 77): $x \\approx 6.08$, round to 6 if integer expected",
